# GovCrawler reverse proxy — Caddy 2
#
# TLS is controlled entirely by the DOMAIN env var (set in .env):
#
#   DOMAIN=app.yourorg.com   — Caddy auto-provisions a Let's Encrypt cert.
#                              Needs a public DNS A record + ports 80/443 open.
#
#   DOMAIN=:80               — Plain HTTP on port 80. No cert, no redirect.
#                              Use this for localhost testing (see override.yml)
#                              or when TLS is terminated upstream.
#
# Org LAN with internal CA (no public internet):
#   Set DOMAIN=govcrawler.internal and add `tls internal` inside the site block
#   below, then run once: docker compose exec proxy caddy trust
#   to install the Caddy root CA on org machines.

{$DOMAIN} {
	reverse_proxy api:8001
}
